-- Ecobank Guinea Says 2011 Profit More Than Doubled
-- B y   O u g n a   C a m a r a
-- 2012-03-01T10:27:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-01/ecobank-guinea-says-2011-profit-more-than-doubled-correct-.html
(Corrects figures in first paragraph to millions.)  Ecobank Transnational Inc. (ETI) ’s Guinean
unit said profit for the year through December rose to 71
million Guinean francs, from 30.2 million francs a year earlier.  Customer deposits increased 43 percent to 2.3 billion
francs from 1.6 billion francs in 2010, the Conakry-based lender
said in a statement handed to reporters in the capital
yesterday.  “Loans granted increased to 1.1 billion francs from 225
million francs,” it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ougna Camara in Conakry at 
 ocamara@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
